## QUESTION 4

1. __Using the new weather variable calculated above, create a boxplot showing the distribution of flights delayed by weather for each season. Describe what you learn from this graph.__    

_Winter has the highest median and variability, showing that weather delays in Winter are more frequent and unpredictable during the first three months of the year. There are also several outliers in Winter and Fall, showing that severe blizzards and other weather events cause massive spikes in delays. Spring is the safest time to fly, so April through June is generally the most reliable for flight schedules._

::: {#429de6e4 .cell execution_count=6}
``` {.python .cell-code}
df_plot = (
    df.filter(pl.col("season") != "Unknown")
    .with_columns(
        pl.col("season").cast(pl.Enum(["Winter", "Spring", "Summer", "Fall"]))
    )
)

p = (
    ggplot(df_plot, aes(x='season', y='total_weather_delay', fill='season')) 
    + geom_boxplot(show_legend=False, outlier_size=1)
    + labs(
        title="Weather-Related Flight Delays by Season",
        subtitle="Includes 100% Weather, 30% Late Aircraft, and 40-65% NAS delays",
        x="Season",
        y="Flights Delayed (in 1,000s)"
    )
    + theme_minimal2()
    + scale_fill_brewer(type='qual', palette='Set1')
)

p.show()
```

